<h1>LG Washer Bearing Replacement</h1>

<p>A worn drum bearing is what's behind that loud grinding or rumbling your LG washer makes on the spin cycle — and it's one of the bigger repairs we do, but well worth it on a solid machine. We replace the tub bearing and seal on LG front- and top-load washers same-day across LA, with the drum out and the assembly done right so it runs quiet for years. $320–420, OEM parts, one-year warranty on our work. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Signs Your LG Washer Bearing Is Worn</h2>
<p>The tell is noise. A worn bearing makes a loud rumble or grinding that gets noticeably worse as the drum speeds up on the spin cycle, and you can often feel play in the drum by grabbing it and rocking it by hand. Metal-on-metal scraping, or rust streaks weeping from behind the drum, point the same way. A failing bearing also lets the drum wander, so it frequently shows up alongside a machine that shakes and bangs — our guide to an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-shaking/">LG washer shaking and loud</a> covers how we separate a bearing from a balance or suspension problem.</p>

<h2>How We Replace an LG Washer Bearing</h2>
<p>This is a teardown job. Our techs strip the machine down, pull the drum, and on many LG models — the WM3900, WM4000, and WT7300 among them — split the outer tub to reach the bearing. We press out the old bearing and seal, fit a new OEM kit, and reassemble and test the machine through a spin. It runs about 2–3 hours. We always replace the tub seal with the bearing, never on its own, because a leaking seal is usually what wore the bearing out to begin with.</p>

<h2>Cost of Bearing Replacement</h2>
<p>Bearing replacement runs $320–420 installed, depending on the model and how much the tub has to come apart to reach it. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. For the full breakdown of where that number comes from, see our <a href="/washer/price-list/lg-washer-bearing-replacement-cost/">LG washer bearing replacement cost</a> page.</p>

<h2>Why It's Worth Repairing</h2>
<p>A comparable new LG washer runs $800–1,500 delivered and installed, so a $320–420 bearing job is a fraction of replacing the machine and buys another 8–10 years on a washer you already know. That math favors the repair on an otherwise sound machine. If we find other major parts are also failing, we'll give you an honest read so you're not pouring a big repair into a washer near the end of its life.</p>

<h2>Why OEM Parts and a Warranty Matter</h2>
<p>We fit OEM bearing and seal kits, not generic substitutes that wear out faster, and back the work with a one-year warranty on parts and labor. On a teardown this involved, doing it once with the right parts is what keeps the drum quiet for years instead of months.</p>

<p>Hearing a grinding rumble on spin? Our LG Dryer Repair techs handle bearing replacements same-day across LA, Orange County, and Ventura County — we confirm the cause on-site before any teardown. Call (323) 990-7550; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Bearing Replacement</h2>

<h3>How do I know if my LG washer needs a new bearing?</h3>
<p>A worn LG washer bearing makes a loud grinding or rumbling noise that gets worse during the spin cycle, and the drum often has visible play when you push it by hand. You may also see rust streaks or hear metal-on-metal — that's the bearing, and it won't fix itself.</p>

<h3>How much does LG washer bearing replacement cost?</h3>
<p>Bearing replacement runs $320–420 installed, depending on the model and whether the tub has to be split to reach it. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and we use OEM bearing and seal kits with a one-year warranty. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Is it worth replacing the bearing or should I buy a new LG washer?</h3>
<p>For most machines, replacing the bearing is worth it — $320–420 versus $800–1,500 for a comparable new LG washer, and a bearing job buys another 8–10 years. We'll tell you straight on-site if other major parts are also failing and a replacement makes more sense.</p>

<h3>Why does the bearing and seal get replaced together?</h3>
<p>The tub seal sits right at the bearing and fails alongside it — a leaking seal is usually what destroyed the bearing in the first place by letting water in. Replacing the bearing without the seal just sets up another failure, so we always do both as a kit.</p>

<h3>How long does LG washer bearing replacement take?</h3>
<p>It's typically a 2–3 hour job because the drum has to come out and, on many LG models, the tub gets split to reach the bearing. We do it same-day in most cases and reassemble and test before we leave.</p>

